article.headline: Penn State 73, Lehigh 64
article.story: STATE COLLEGE, Pa. (AP) -- Aaron Johnson scored 25 points and grabbed 12 rebounds as Penn State defeated Lehigh 73-64 on Friday. It was the home opener for the Nittany Lions (2-2), who won their seventh straight over the defending Patriot League champion Mountain Hawks (0-1). With the score tied 36-36 midway through the second half, Penn State went on an 11-4 run, getting five points from Marlon Smith, who finished with 16 on the game. Lehigh pulled within three with 45 seconds to play, but Penn State closed the game out by shooting 8-of-8 from the free-throw line. Joe Knight led the Hawks with 23 points and keyed a 17-6 run toward the end of the first half in which he hit four straight 3-pointers to pull Lehigh within four at halftime, 31-27. Knight finished the game shooting 7-of-15 from the field, including 5-of-10 on 3-pointers. Travis Parker had 12 points and Geary Claxton had 11 for the Nittany Lions, while Lehigh got 13 points off the bench from Kyle Neptune.
